      date:'January 2026', read:'5 min',
      body:`<h2>Why your logo matters so much</h2>
<p>Your logo is often the first thing prospects see. In a few seconds, it must communicate who you are, what you do, and why you should be trusted. A weak logo undermines your credibility, even if your services are excellent.</p>
<h2>5 steps to create a successful logo</h2>
<h3>1. Define your brand identity</h3>
<p>Before drawing a single shape, answer these questions: What are your company values? Who is your target audience? What feelings do you want to inspire?</p>
<h3>2. Research inspiration</h3>
<p>Analyse your direct competitors' logos. Identify what works and what does not in your sector. Build a visual reference board.</p>
<h3>3. Choose the right logo type</h3>
<p>Logomark (symbol only), wordmark (text only), lettermark (initials), combination mark (text and symbol) or emblem. Each format has its advantages depending on your use.</p>
<h3>4. Master colour and typography</h3>
<p>Colours convey specific emotions. Blue inspires trust, red energy, yellow creativity. Choose a palette of 2 to 3 colours maximum. For typography, avoid overly decorative fonts that harm readability.</p>
<h3>5. Test and validate</h3>
<p>Test your logo on white and black backgrounds, small and large format, and on a coloured background. Ask people outside your project for their opinion.</p>
<h2>Mistakes to avoid</h2>
<p>Avoid overly complex logos, 3D effects that age poorly, generic clip art and logos too similar to existing brands. A good logo must be simple, memorable and timeless.</p>`
